{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Sydney South West Area Health Service |nativename = |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = January 2005 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = (etc.) |dissolved = 31 December 2010 |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = |coordinates = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Carmel Tebbutt]] |minister1_pfo = Minister for Health |minister2_name = |minister2_pfo = (etc.) |chief1_name = [[Mike Wallace]] |chief1_position = Chief Executive Officer |chief2_name = |chief2_position = (etc.) |parent_agency = [[New South Wales Department of Health]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = (etc.) |website = http://www.sswahs.nsw.gov.au |footnotes = }}
'''Sydney South West Area Health Service''', abbreviated '''SSWAHS''' and known by the corporate name '''Sydney South West Health''', was an area health service charged with the provision of public health services in central and south-western [[Sydney, New South Wales|Sydney]]. It was formed in January 2005 from the amalgamation of the former Central Sydney Area Health Service and the South Western Sydney Area Health Service. It was a statutory body of the [[Government of New South Wales|New South Wales Government]], operating under the NSW Department of Health. The head office of SSWAHS was located in [[Liverpool, New South Wales|Liverpool]]. It was disbanded on 1 January 2011 as part of the National Health Reform and creation of Local Hospital Networks, and replaced by the [[Sydney Local Health District]] and [[South Western Sydney Local Health District]].<ref>[http://www.health.nsw.gov.au/initiatives/healthreform/index.asp Health Reform] NSW Health, accessed 4 January 2011.</ref>
==Major facilities== ===Eastern Zone=== The Eastern Zone of SSWAHS comprised the facilities of the former Central Sydney Area Health Service. Major facilities in the Eastern Zone were: *[[Canterbury Hospital]], [[Canterbury, New South Wales|Canterbury]] *[[Concord Repatriation General Hospital]], [[Concord, New South Wales|Concord]] *[[Royal Prince Alfred Hospital]], [[Camperdown, New South Wales|Camperdown]] *[[Concord Centre for Mental Health]], [[Concord, New South Wales|Concord]] (Sydney South West Area Mental Health Service) *[[Sydney Dental Hospital]], [[Surry Hills, New South Wales|Surry Hills]] *[[Balmain Hospital]], [[Balmain, New South Wales|Balmain]]
===Western Zone=== The Western Zone of SSWAHS comprised the facilities of the former South Western Sydney Area Health Service. Major facilities in the Western Zone were: *[[Bankstown Lidcombe Hospital]], [[Bankstown, New South Wales|Bankstown]] *[[Camden Hospital]], [[Camden, New South Wales|Camden]] *[[Campbelltown Hospital]], [[Campbelltown, New South Wales|Campbelltown]] *[[Fairfield Hospital (Sydney)|Fairfield Hospital]], [[Fairfield, New South Wales|Fairfield]] *[[Liverpool Hospital]], [[Liverpool, New South Wales|Liverpool]] *[[Bowral Hospital]], [[Bowral, New South Wales|Bowral]]
