'''ZIMA Medical Science & Educational Trust''' (''ஜிமா மருத்துவ அறிவியல் & கல்வி அறக்கட்டளை'' in Tamil) is an [[India]]n Non-Profit and Non-Governmental Organization which was established in 2005 and a registered [[Society]] of Tamil Nadu Government.
==History==
The ZIMA Medical Science Educational Trust is a registered society, which was established in the year 2005 under the leadership of Dr.K.M.Z.Hussain. The Trust has the objective of imparting education in the field of Medicine.
==AIMS==
ZIMA Medical Science and Educational Trust is a non-profit, non-governmental organization registered under the Societies' Registration Act of 1860 in 2005, and since then have been raising resources to isolate poverty, illiteracy, population, epidemiology and insanitary. ZIMA raises its activities to the people of India without any motivate of profit, irrespective of caste, community, creed or religion. ZIMA's main voices are to respect our Nation and Freedom Fighters. [[File:Mumbai-street-kids.jpg|thumb|right|200px]]
==Focus==
ZIMA focusing many areas to develop Indian youths knowledge. Mainly focused areas are: * Arts and Humanities * Criminal Justice * Education Energy * Environment * Health * Labor Employment * Populations * Rural Development * Youth Future * National Education * Social Medicine * Society and Culture * Substance Abuse * Technology [[File:Ziiimaa.png|thumb|left|400px]]
The specific objectives are: * To assist in the provision of quality education to Indian Youths. * To assist in the provision of a well rounded education for Indians to become good citizens. * To offer bursaries for needy Indian at degree level. * To assist Indians train in courses such as driving and dressmaking if this helps lift up family standards.
